other_tests.findings: Bone biopsy before teriparatide was compatible with a bone mineralization defect with very wide osteoid seams and no osteoblasts observed. Five months after teriparatide, the extent of bone surface covered with osteoid was greater, the interface between osteoid and mineralized bone was well demarcated, and osteoblast numbers were increased.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Initial biopsy showed large osteoid seams with no osteoblasts. After 5 months on teriparatide, more osteoid was present, and osteoblast activity increased, but very wide osteoid seams remained. Four months after stopping teriparatide, wide osteoid seams were present again with no osteoblasts.

other_tests.findings: Two missense mutations (Ala176Thr and Val423Ala) and one polymorphism (Val522Ala) were identified in the TNSALP gene.
